race.comment: SKY SISTA (10) was out of the money when resuming from a spell last start over 1300m at Sandown-Hillside, beaten 5.5 lengths after being in contention on the corner. Finds an easier assignment and can get the job done. RENTESSIS (8) resumes having had three trials in readiness. Was last seen when winning on debut at Wangaratta where he put a margin on his rivals. WRIGLEY FIELD (13) hit the ground running first up when saluting at Swan Hill. Fitter for the run. RUNAWAY SOUL (3) proved too strong two runs ago at Ballarat. Not as effective last time out when fifth over 1300m at this track, beaten 4 lengths. Perfectly placed and is sure to take plenty of stopping. Good depth to the race with SWIFT CIRCLE (6) and JUGIONG (2) other chances.
